BENGALURU &ndash; Copper miner Kaz Minerals said its first-quarter copper production more than doubled from a year earlier, helped by output from its new Bozshakol and Aktogay mines, in Kazakhastan. The company&#39;s stock rose as much as 4.9% to &pound;5.025 on the London Stock Exchange, making it the top FTSE midcap gainer. The company, focused on large-scale, low-cost open pit mining in Kazakhstan, said its copper output stood at 52 000 t in the first quarter ended March 31. Gold production also rose 140.1% to 42 500 oz. The company said it was on track to meet 2017 production guidance for all metals.